In a letter addressed to the members of the Federal Workforce, President Joe Biden expresses his gratitude and appreciation for their dedication and service to the nation. He credits their tireless work for the progress made in various areas, including confronting the pandemic, fueling the economy's recovery, addressing the climate crisis, advancing racial equity, and protecting national security. While acknowledging that there are still challenges ahead, the President emphasizes the importance of building on the innovations and technologies utilized during the pandemic to make the government more efficient and effective. He also mentions the possibility of increasing in-person work while ensuring the health and safety of the workforce. President Biden concludes by thanking the federal employees and their families for their service and sacrifices, expressing his optimism for the future of America with their continued dedication and leadership.